pptpProfileTable.name: pptpProfileTable
pptpProfileTable.description: The pptpProfileTable contains parameters for the Point-to-Point Tunneling Protocol (PPTP) according RFC 2637. Entries are removed by setting an entry's pptpProfileKeepalive object to 'delete'.

pptpProfileId.name: pptpProfileId
pptpProfileId.description: The profile ID of the PPTP profile.

pptpProfileKeepalive.name: pptpProfileKeepalive
pptpProfileKeepalive.description: When set to on(1), PPTP echo requests as described in RFC 2637 are sent in regular intervals during the connection. If set to off(2), no PPTP echo requests will be performed, delete(3) determines the entry is marked for discard.

pptpProfileMaxRequests.name: pptpProfileMaxRequests
pptpProfileMaxRequests.description: The maximum number of outstanding PPTP echo replies, until the PPTP control connection is droped and all associated calls are terminated.

pptpProfileMaxBlockTime.name: pptpProfileMaxBlockTime
pptpProfileMaxBlockTime.description: Maximum time (in msec) the GRE Send Window is blocked. If the GRE Send Window is full, no packets can be forwarded and the Maximum Time is passed, the GRE Send Window is resetted to prevent unsolvable situations.

pptpProfileMaxAckTimeout.name: pptpProfileMaxAckTimeout
pptpProfileMaxAckTimeout.description: Maximum value the adaptive Acknowledgment Timeout (in msec) can reach while it is calculated. According to RFC 2637.

pptpProfileReassemblyTimeout.name: pptpProfileReassemblyTimeout
pptpProfileReassemblyTimeout.description: Maximum time (in msec) for rearranging out-of-sequence packets. After this time outstanding packets will be supposed missing.

pptpCtlConnTable.name: pptpCtlConnTable
pptpCtlConnTable.description: The pptpCtlConnTable displays all currently active PPTP dontrol connections Only the system can add or remove entries to this table. Creating entries: Entries are added when an outgoing or incoming TCP connection (port 1723) is established. Deleting entries: Entries are removed once the respective PPTP control connection is disconnected.

pptpCtlConnOriginator.name: pptpCtlConnOriginator
pptpCtlConnOriginator.description: The originator of the PPTP control connection.

pptpCtlConnAge.name: pptpCtlConnAge
pptpCtlConnAge.description: The age of the PPTP control connection. The format is in hh:mm:ss.00.

pptpCtlConnState.name: pptpCtlConnState
pptpCtlConnState.description: The state of the PPTP control connection according RFC 2637.

pptpCtlConnRemoteIpAddress.name: pptpCtlConnRemoteIpAddress
pptpCtlConnRemoteIpAddress.description: The IP address of the remote PPTP tunnel endpoint.

pptpCtlConnLocalIpAddress.name: pptpCtlConnLocalIpAddress
pptpCtlConnLocalIpAddress.description: The IP address of the local PPTP tunnel endpoint.

pptpCtlConnVersion.name: pptpCtlConnVersion
pptpCtlConnVersion.description: This variable contains the negotiated PPTP version.

pptpCtlConnHost.name: pptpCtlConnHost
pptpCtlConnHost.description: DNS name of the issuing PAC or PNS.

pptpCtlConnVendor.name: pptpCtlConnVendor
pptpCtlConnVendor.description: Vendor specific string describing the type of PAC or PNS being used on remote side.

pptpCtlConnFirmRev.name: pptpCtlConnFirmRev
pptpCtlConnFirmRev.description: This variable contains the firmware revision number of the issuing PAC or PNS.

pptpCallTable.name: pptpCallTable
pptpCallTable.description: The pptpCallTable displays all currently active PPTP calls (incoming and outgoing). Only the system can add or remove entries to this table. Creating entries: Entries are added when an outgoing call is made or when an incoming call is connected. Deleting entries: Entries are removed once the respective call is disconnected.

pptpCallDirection.name: pptpCallDirection
pptpCallDirection.description: Direction of the PPTP call, incoming(1) or outgoing(2).

pptpCallAge.name: pptpCallAge
pptpCallAge.description: The age of the call. For outgoing calls, the time since the call began, or for incoming calls, the time since the call was received. The format is in hh:mm:ss.00.

pptpCallState.name: pptpCallState
pptpCallState.description: The state of the PPTP call according RFC 2637.

pptpCallRemoteIpAddress.name: pptpCallRemoteIpAddress
pptpCallRemoteIpAddress.description: The called (for outgoing calls) or calling IP address (for incoming calls).

pptpCallLocalIpAddress.name: pptpCallLocalIpAddress
pptpCallLocalIpAddress.description: The calling (for outgoing calls) or called IP address (for incoming calls).

pptpCallReceivedPackets.name: pptpCallReceivedPackets
pptpCallReceivedPackets.description: Count of received valid GRE-encapsulated packets.

pptpCallReceivedErrors.name: pptpCallReceivedErrors
pptpCallReceivedErrors.description: Count of received invalid GRE-encapsulated packets.

pptpCallInfo.name: pptpCallInfo
pptpCallInfo.description: Additional information to identify the PPTP call

pptpCreditsTable.name: pptpCreditsTable
pptpCreditsTable.description: The pptpCreditsTable contains informations about current used resources and maximum allowed resources for each during a specified interval subsystem. Creating entries: Entries are added by the system during startup. Deleting entries: Is not possible.

pptpCreditsMeasuretime.name: pptpCreditsMeasuretime
pptpCreditsMeasuretime.description: Time of one observation interval in seconds.

pptpCreditsMaxInCon.name: pptpCreditsMaxInCon
pptpCreditsMaxInCon.description: Maximum number of allowed incoming connections during the observation interval. -1 disables this limit.

pptpCreditsMaxOutCon.name: pptpCreditsMaxOutCon
pptpCreditsMaxOutCon.description: Maximum number of allowed outgoing connections during the observation interval. -1 disables this limit.

pptpCreditsMaxInDuration.name: pptpCreditsMaxInDuration
pptpCreditsMaxInDuration.description: Maximum connect time for incoming connections in seconds during the observation interval. -1 disables this limit.

pptpCreditsMaxOutDuration.name: pptpCreditsMaxOutDuration
pptpCreditsMaxOutDuration.description: Maximum connect time for outgoing connections in seconds during the observation interval. -1 disables this limit

pptpCreditsTimeleft.name: pptpCreditsTimeleft
pptpCreditsTimeleft.description: Time in seconds left in current interval. Writing to Timeleft will restart the observation interval.

pptpCreditsTotalInCon.name: pptpCreditsTotalInCon
pptpCreditsTotalInCon.description: Total count of incoming connections during the observation interval.

pptpCreditsTotalOutCon.name: pptpCreditsTotalOutCon
pptpCreditsTotalOutCon.description: Total count of outgoing connections during the observation interval.

pptpCreditsTotalMaxCon.name: pptpCreditsTotalMaxCon
pptpCreditsTotalMaxCon.description: Maximum number of simultaniously established connections during the observation interval.

pptpCreditsTotalInDuration.name: pptpCreditsTotalInDuration
pptpCreditsTotalInDuration.description: Total connect time of incoming connections during the observation interval.

pptpCreditsTotalOutDuration.name: pptpCreditsTotalOutDuration
pptpCreditsTotalOutDuration.description: Total connect time of outgoing connections during the observation interval.

pptpCreditsMaxCurrentInCon.name: pptpCreditsMaxCurrentInCon
pptpCreditsMaxCurrentInCon.description: Maximum number of currently allowed incoming connections. -1 disables this limit.

pptpCreditsMaxCurrentOutCon.name: pptpCreditsMaxCurrentOutCon
pptpCreditsMaxCurrentOutCon.description: Maximum number of currently allowed outgoing connections. -1 disables this limit.

pptpCreditsMaxCurrentCon.name: pptpCreditsMaxCurrentCon
pptpCreditsMaxCurrentCon.description: Maximum number of currently allowed connections in both directions. -1 disables this limit.
